(18918, 654, 'content_segment_0_content', '<h4><strong>Access around the site</strong></h4>\r\nThe Plot event takes place at Eastnor Castle Deer Park. Please see the parks <a href=\"https://eastnorcastle.com/visit-eastnor-castle/eastnor-deer-park/\">website</a>for more information.\r\n\r\nThe site is a green field site with some sloping areas around the event site and the event entrances. The event field is park land therefore some areas within the site will be uneven. There are no hard standing pathways once in the event site. The majority of stages will be, on average, 60 to 70 metres apart.\r\n\r\nIf you require any of the following access facilities during Plot Festival please purchase your tickets as normal and complete the Access Application Form once it becomes available.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Personal Assistant Tickets</li>\r\n 	<li>Viewing Platform Access</li>\r\n 	<li>Accessible Car Parking Space</li>\r\n 	<li>Use of Accessible Toilets</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you need a Personal Assistant to accompany you at the festival or Accessible Car Parking, please<b>DO NOT </b>purchase these extras as these are applied for separately via the Access Application Form.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>Bookable access facilities</strong></h4>\r\nThe location of the disabled car park will be within 5 minutes of an event entrance\r\n\r\nThe event will take place in the Papal Field in Heaton Park, all entrances to the park will be accessible.\r\n\r\nThe following access facilities need to be pre-booked using the Access Requirement Form. This form and the required evidence must be sent to us once you have purchased a ticket.\r\n\r\n<strong>1)2 for 1 Tickets for Personal Assistants</strong>\r\n\r\nWe provide a 2 for 1 ticket scheme for individuals who would be unable to attend our events without bringing a personal assistant. Once you have bought a full price ticket, please fill in the Access Requirement Form and provide us with evidence as listed on the form in order to receive your personal assistant ticket.\r\n\r\n<strong>2)Viewing Platform Wristband</strong>\r\n\r\nA viewing platform will be located within the Main Stage arena. In order to gain access to a viewing platform, you need a viewing platform wristband.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><b>How to Apply</b></h4>\r\nIf you wish to apply for any of the above facilities at Plot Festival, you will be able to do so once the application form becomes available on this page shortly.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime, you can order your tickets, less one adult ticket if you are to be applying for a PA ticket.\r\n\r\nYou will get the option to select you require Access at the time of booking and we will contact you with the application form when they become available.'),
