(25688, 738, 'content_segment_0_content', 'Plot Festival is a UK music and performing arts festival, set each year in the beautiful Eastnor Castle Deer Park. Laid back and popular with families, Plot\'s lineup spans music, comedy, poetry, theatre, politics, film and workshops across its weekend.\r\n\r\n2019\'s lineup will include headline sets from Jon Mills, Bazzy Star and Bobbins, while its hugely diverse programme will also feature theatre productions from esteemed companies such as Sadler\'s Wells.\r\n\r\nTake a wander around the site, and you\'re just as likely to stumble across woodland film screenings, live art and the sanctuary of wellbeing, where you can relax amongst ambient soundscapes or get involved with some yoga.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-733\" src=\"http://plot.test/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/About2-1024x617.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"617\" />\r\n\r\nPlot Festival is a community event oriented towards live performances of singing and instrument playing that is often presented with a theme such as musical genre (e.g., blues, folk, jazz, classical music), nationality, or locality of musicians, or holiday. Plot is held outdoors, with tents or roofed temporary stages for the performers. We host other attractions such as food and merchandise vending, dance, crafts, performance art, and social or cultural activities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
